## What this is
GPRTool is a browser-based CAD PWA for calculating Green Plot Ratio (GPR), a greenery metric invented by Boon Ong (Ong 2003, 460+ citations). It renders a 3D scene via Three.js with two viewports (2D plan + 3D perspective), lets users import building geometry (OBJ/glTF/DXF), place plants from an LAI database, and compute GPR scores. Stack: vanilla HTML/CSS/JS + Three.js r160, no npm, no frameworks. Deployed on Vercel via GitHub (root: app/). Use Microsoft Edge for development -- Chrome has rendering issues.

